========================================================
  6v6 Attacker - pentest learning console
========================================================

Installed tools:
  nmap, hydra, sqlmap, nikto, ncat, pwntools

Network topology (4-tier chained):
  ext (10.20.30.0/24)  <- you are here (10.20.30.202)
       |
       v   default route via fw (10.20.30.1)
  fw (10.20.30.1) ext + (10.20.31.1) pipe
       |
       v
  ips (10.20.31.2) pipe + (10.20.32.1) dmz   <- Suricata IDS
       |
       v
  dmz (10.20.32.0/24): web, siem, portal, wazuh-*
       |
       v   web acts as WAF (Apache + ModSec)
  int (10.20.40.0/24): juiceshop, dvwa, neobank, ...

All HTTP attacks traverse: attacker -> fw -> ips -> web -> vuln
Internal services (siem, dashboard, portal): -> fw -> ips -> [target]

Quick start:
  curl http://juice.6v6.lab/                    (vuln, via WAF)
  curl -A 'sqlmap/1.7' http://juice.6v6.lab/    (WAF blocks, IDS alerts)
  nmap -sT -p 80,443 10.20.32.80                (web direct, via fw+ips)
  nikto -h http://juice.6v6.lab/

Browse SIEM (no WAF in path):
  https://siem.6v6.lab/   (admin / SecretPassword)
